Their bowlers laid the platform for a memorable victory against their mighty neighbours by restricting India to 148-6 at the Arun Jaitley Stadium. Mushfiqur, dropped in the deep on 38, made 60 not out and featured in a crucial partnership with Soumya Sarkar as Bangladesh finally humbled India in this format at the ninth attempt. Rajkot hosts the second Twenty20 of the three-match series on Thursday. --Reuters--